2.12	Clara_Shortridge_Foltz	Clara S. Foltz	Clara Shortridge Foltz (July 16, 1849 â€“ September 2, 1934) was the first female lawyer on the West Coast. She was the sister of U.S. Senator Samuel M. Shortridge. The Criminal Courts Building in downtown Los Angeles was renamed after her in 2002, and is now known as the Clara Shortridge Foltz Criminal Justice Center.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bb/Clara_Shortridge_Foltz.jpg/275px-Clara_Shortridge_Foltz.jpg
